# Java Developer Interview Questions

Java developer interview questions covering various topics from core Java concepts to advanced Java EE frameworks and problem-solving.

## Core Java Concepts

| No. | Question |
| --- | -------- |
| 1. | What are the main principles of Object-Oriented Programming (OOP)? |
| 2. | Explain the differences between abstract classes and interfaces. |
| 3. | What is method overloading and method overriding? Give examples. |
| 4. | What are the differences between checked and unchecked exceptions? |
| 5. | Explain the `final`, `finally`, and `finalize` keywords in Java. |
| 6. | What are access modifiers in Java? Explain `private`, `protected`, `default`, and `public`. |
| 7. | What is polymorphism in Java? How does it support OOP principles? |
| 8. | Describe the significance of the `static` keyword in Java. |
| 9. | What is the difference between `==` and `.equals()` method in Java? When would you use each? |
| 10. | How does Java handle multithreading? Discuss synchronization and thread safety. |
| 11. | Explain the concept of Java collections framework. Discuss `List`, `Set`, and `Map` interfaces. |
| 12. | What is the difference between `ArrayList` and `LinkedList`? When would you use one over the other? |
| 13. | How does Java support handling of null values? Discuss `Optional` class. |
| 14. | What are generics in Java? Provide an example of how they are used. |
| 15. | How does Java manage memory? Explain stack and heap memory. |
| 16. | Discuss the lifecycle of a Java object. |
| 17. | What is the difference between stack memory and heap memory in Java? |

## Java EE and Frameworks

| No. | Question |
| --- | -------- |
| 18. | What is Spring Framework? Explain its core modules. |
| 19. | What are the benefits of using Spring Boot over traditional Spring Framework? |
| 20. | Explain Dependency Injection (DI) and Inversion of Control (IoC) in the context of Spring. |
| 21. | What is Hibernate? How does it differ from JDBC? |
| 22. | How do RESTful web services work in Java? Discuss `@RestController` and `@RequestMapping`. |
| 23. | What are the key features of Java Servlets? How do they differ from JSP? |
| 24. | Explain the concept of Bean Validation (JSR 380) in Java EE applications. |
| 25. | Discuss the role of annotations in Spring MVC applications. |
| 26. | How does Spring Security work? Explain authentication and authorization processes. |

## Testing and Debugging

| No. | Question |
| --- | -------- |
| 27. | What are unit tests and integration tests? How do you implement them in Java? |
| 28. | Explain the importance of logging in Java applications. Discuss popular logging frameworks. |
| 29. | How would you debug a Java application? Discuss tools and techniques you would use. |
| 30. | What is mocking in Java testing? Discuss Mockito framework. |

## Advanced Java Concepts

| No. | Question |
| --- | -------- |
| 31. | What is serialization in Java? How do you implement it? |
| 32. | Discuss the concept of Java memory management, including garbage collection. |
| 33. | Explain the principles of design patterns. Discuss any Java-specific design patterns you know. |
| 34. | What are lambdas and functional interfaces? How are they used in Java? |
| 35. | Discuss the differences between Java 8 and Java 11 (or the latest version). |
| 36. | How does Java handle concurrent programming? Discuss `java.util.concurrent` package. |

## Problem-Solving and Algorithms

| No. | Question |
| --- | -------- |
| 37. | Implement a binary search algorithm in Java. |
| 38. | Write code to reverse a linked list in Java. |
| 39. | Discuss the time complexity of various sorting algorithms (e.g., bubble sort, merge sort). |
| 40. | Implement a stack or queue using Java collections framework. |
| 41. | Write a program to find duplicate elements in an array. |
| 42. | Explain the concept of Big O notation. How is it relevant to algorithm analysis? |

